        <body>
            <listPerson>
                <person sex="1">
                    <persName xml:lang="gez" xml:id="n1">ገብረ፡ ሚካኤል፡</persName>
                    <persName xml:lang="gez" type="normalized" corresp="#n1">Gabra Mikāʾel</persName>
                    <persName xml:lang="ar" xml:id="n2">ميخائيل الحبشي</persName>
                    <persName xml:lang="ar" type="normalized" corresp="#n2">Mīhāʾīl al-Ḥabašī</persName>
                    <persName><roleName type="title">qummuṣ</roleName></persName>
                    <occupation type="ecclesiastic">A monk and consecrated priest who resided in
                        <placeName ref="INS0478DS">Dayr as-Suryān</placeName> in the
                        19th or early 20th century.</occupation>
                    <residence>He is associated with <placeName ref="INS0354DB"/> and 
                        <placeName ref="INS0352EA"/> in the manuscripts attesting him.</residence>
                    <floruit notBefore="1875" notAfter="1960"/>
                    <note>
                        <p>The modern Arabic manuscript description placed on a paper sheet inside <ref type="mss" corresp="DSEthiop13"/> states
                        that Mīḫāʾīl al-Ḥabašī was born in <placeName ref="LOC1178AddiNa"/> in Eritrea and that his mother's name was
                        <foreign xml:lang="ar">Lītā Māryām</foreign>, possibly a transcription of <foreign xml:lang="gez">Walatta Māryām</foreign>.
                            In <ref type="mss" corresp="DSEthiop9"/>, the name of <persName ref="PRS12967WalattaM"/> was erased 
                            and substituted with that of <persName ref="PRS12002Gabrami"/>. There is no indication in the manuscript as to whether both
                        persons were related.</p>
                        
                      <p>  The <ref target="https://stmaryrodelfarag.com/%D8%A7%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%A1-%D8%B3%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%82%D9%8A%D9%86/">website of the 
                            church St Mary in Rawḍ al-Farag in Cairo</ref> states that a <foreign xml:lang="ar">qummuṣ</foreign> Mīḫāʾīl al-Ḥabašī lived in 
                          this church, until 
                          <persName ref="PRS3260CyrilVI"/> ordered all monks to return to their monasteries. This decree was issued by Cyril VI in 1960, 
                          <bibl><ptr target="bm:OMahony2007Tradition"/><citedRange unit="page">171</citedRange></bibl>.
                          Since it was impossible for him to return to his native country, he went to <placeName ref="INS0478DS"/>, 
                          were he died.  Whether this person is identical with the Gabra Mikāʾel/Mīḫāʾīl al-Ḥabašī mentioned in the manuscripts of
                        <placeName ref="INS0478DS"/> can only be speculated.</p>
                        
                       <p> It cannot be excluded that Gabra Mikāʾel mentioned in the manuscripts <ref type="mss" corresp="DSEthiop9"/>,
                        <ref type="mss" corresp="DSEthiop10"/> and <ref type="mss" corresp="DSEthiop13"/> might refer to more than one person.</p>
                    </note>
                </person>
